<h4>Pots and Pans</h4>
<p>Stack and nest smaller pots and pans into larger ones to save space. Depending on the size of the pans, you may need a large box. Use towels, or wadded up packing paper, to stuff around the pans in the box. This step will provide support and padding. Wrap glass lids in packing paper (no need to wrap metal lids) and place them around the pots, or pack all the lids together in a separate, smaller box.</p>
<h4>Food Items</h4>
<p>Pack nonperishable items separately from perishable food. Start by decluttering your pantry. Discard any expired items and donate usable food that you do not want to move to a food bank. Anything open should be securely closed before placing it into a box. Use a cooler to transport perishable items. However, it may be wiser to discard perishables, or give usable items to a neighbor or friend, instead of moving them, especially if you are moving long-distance.</p>

